=Description=

"Three steps to a Creativist Society:

1) In January 2010, Olivia Sprinkel’s ‘Creativist Manifesto’ was published on Changethis.com

2) In February 2010, Arnold Beekes got in touch with Olivia via Twitter to ask what her plans for Creativist were. Conversations ensued.

3) In May 2010, Olivia and Arnold launched the Creativist Society website, to create a space for people to share their vision of society what can be at its best - at work, at play, in our relationships, in our communities - and when creativity is a core organising principle. So join in by contributing your thoughts, your experiences, your examples of what you are doing - this space is really what you make it. This is a ‘bumping place’ for ideas, people, projects, inspiration. So get bumping!  Join in the discussion about one of the articles, or submit your own - details about this are on the submit page, but the main one is: it is very easy to do."
(http://www.creativistsociety.com/about)

